summary: Andi Mack and Raven’s Home sharing the same session what a powerful combo. Disney is honestly dumb for never (or rarely) airing...
question: Andi Mack and Raven’s Home sharing the same session what a powerful combo. Disney is honestly dumb for never (or rarely) airing them together during their time on the air...
answer:
It’s interesting that they squeezed Coop & Cami, Sydney to the Max, and Bunk’d all into one session, and that Bizaardvark stars are scheduled to appear but aren’t included in any of the main-stage events. But pairing Andi Mack and Raven’s Home shows that they’re aware of where their power lies.

I wouldn’t call them dumb for not airing the two shows together though. It’s clear that they usually spread them out intentionally in hopes of the views from each show carrying over to their less successful series as an attempt to boost those ratings.
